I would agree with this.  Save TAUNT for when the mobs turns abruptly.  Pressing TAUNT when you have agro doesnt do anything except make the TAUNT button unavailible for when its needed.<br>
<br>
When I fight PoS giants I regularly turn ATK off while I am waiting for that heal so I dont take as many ripostes (using 2hs epic with PB1)  I leave the TAUNT key availible incase somone grabs agro while my ATK is off.  Side note, I never kick anymore, something sucks about getting a 600 dmg riposte from a kick.  <br>
<br>
I seldom if ever loose agro for more then one round of atk or a quick TAUNT press, mob turns, I ATK and TAUNT, mob back on me, I turn ATK off wait for heal, re ATK.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp. Im 62, im not uber but I group with some 65 monks, rogues, rangers and a pali with weapons far superior than my little 2hs epic and I rarely have any issues, even when those darn Ocean Giants proc Feighn Death on me. <p><center><IMG SRC="http://home.cfl.rr.com/bastionamici/Sigs/Faederya_Faedilenew.gif" WIDTH=490 HEIGHT=200 BORDER=0 USEMAP="#Faederya_Faedilenew.gif">
