As I stated the figours, were just made up, as a factor to make people understand the general idea.<br>
<br>
I can say though that taunt in my opinion, is an added aggro numeric value. Not a one way trip to the top of the hate list... Was playing around last night PLing a freind. <br>
Zone: Velks Lab<br>
Mobs: Random Junk<br>
Char/equip: 65war 190ish aa, blade of war 71% haste self buffed.<br>
<br>
I was pling a lower level war friend for 30 mins or so, and encountered this one tidbit. If I melee'd a mob for 20 seconds, down to 50% or so. . .The other war when I asked him, could not taunt it off me until he had pressed taunt an average of 8 times. . .<br>
<br>
Minimal amount of times he clicked it before gaining aggro was 4, max was 16 I beleive.<br>
<br>
Your not going to tell me that over about 15 mobs, he consecutivly failed taunt 7 times on average....Hence he was building aggro, towards myself and beyond...<br>
<br>
The same occured on the last few mobs if I only did about 20% damage before he started taunting (i was not taunting and he was not meleeing prior either), which leads me to the conclusion that there is also a hate cap. Something I have speculated for four years, and seen in practice almost every day.<br>
<br>
I dont know the figours and for the life of me, couldnt care less what they are. But I do know that in every small test I do no matter what the class, I get the same sort of results.<br>
<br>
I dont know how the above poste\r said he can succesfully taunt aggro away from someone after just sitting and watching them beat the crap through it. It just does not seem logical in the programming and in practice. If I am on a friends war, and want to turn AoW around on enrage so he kills everyone (its good for a laugh, trust me). In the now 20ish times I have done it, I have never goten aggro until at least the fifth or sixth taunt at least...Not rock solid, but if your trying to claim that your supposed taunt check fails THAT often, it would be more efficient to just save you energy and type rude emotes at the mob instead of clicking taunt because it only works 5% of the time.<br>
<br>
It just doesnt make sence. In summary, spamming Taunt sucks, and (in my opinion) taunt is not a one way trip to the top of the hate list. I know at times it can seem like this as you can be just below on the hate list than the person who has aggro, and as such, move up easily /shrug, seems to fit for me. <br>
<br>
Try this...<br>
<br>
