<br>
I 2-box an enchanter(64) and a warrior(65) about 90% of the time. Ever since I hit 60(or maybe it starts working at 61 - someone here can correct me) on the war, I have been able to do the following.<br>
<br>
Pull a mob to camp (usually some random camp in PoV), cast (Howl of Tashan) immediately, then taunt the split second after it lands. As soon as the taunt button refreshes, cast (Forlorn Deeds), then taunt the split second after it lands. The mob turns nearly every taunt. And there is no way that I am overcoming tash-hate and slow-hate with whatever dps i'm putting out in those 6+ seconds between taunts. As an added bonus, I now have solid aggro due to acquiring tash+slow hate.<br>
<br>
So, 1) you are right, spamming taunt doesn't do much but 2) you are absolutely wrong in thinking taunt is numerical.<br>
