<br>
I guess your lucky, cuz even when I keep taunt for after I cast tash, the mob almost always goes straight for the enchanter.<br>
<br>
What I do, is pull, engage the mob, then slow without tashing, since the resist rate at 65 are much lower, and start cheal.<br>
<br>
Playing the slower, and healer makes ya understand a lot about whats going on.<br>
<br>
If I get an early EB proc, I just tash/slow right away as I will not get the enchanter beaten to a pulp.<br>
<br>
With all the aa, and hp I've gotten recently, its just smart to take the time to build aggro before tashing/slowing.<br>
<br>
Sometimes the mobs react weirdly, I'll get 2 EB proc, and then tash, and the mob will run for the enchanter...<br>
<br>
My only firm conclusion on aggro, is to never take anything for granted. <p>Overlord of the brell server<br>
